"Stay Safe Online" Checklist

As a Student Digital Ambassador, here are the 8 essential safety rules to follow:

Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA):- Activate 2FA on your VIT email, GitHub, and social media accounts to add a second layer of security.

Verify before you click:- Hover over links in emails to see the actual URL. If it looks suspicious or uses a URL shortener (like bit.ly) for official work, do not click it.

Use Unique Passwords:- Never use your VIT registration number or date of birth as a password. Use a mix of symbols, numbers, and letters.

UPI Safety:- PIN for Sending Only: Remember that you never need to enter your UPI PIN to receive money. If a "buyer" asks you to enter your PIN to get a payment, it is a scam.

UPI Safety: - Official Apps Only: Only use trusted apps like BHIM, GPay, or PhonePe. Never enter your UPI details on a website reached via an SMS link.

Public Wi-Fi Caution:- Avoid logging into your bank or college portal (V-TOP) while using free public Wi-Fi. Use a VPN or your mobile data instead.

Check App Permissions:- Regularly review which apps have access to your camera, contacts, and microphone. Delete apps you no longer use.

Report Immediately (National Helpline 1930):- If you are a victim of financial fraud, call 1930 or report it at www.cybercrime.gov.in within the "Golden Hour" (first 2 hours) to increase the chances of freezing the stolen funds.
